This paper discusses spectral clustering, which is a popular machine learning technique for clustering nodes in a graph. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the gap between eigenvalues, which is a topic in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Spectral Theory (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the quality guarantee and algorithmic results, which are topics in Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
